The interrogation passage spans several paragraphs in `cynewulf-elene-d2d132`, chapter 1. Starting at **p-534627**, Helena arrives in Jerusalem and summons the Jews "to test them with questions." At **p-7b1c1f**, she assembles 3,000 chosen men from the Jewish people and harangues them about their rejection of Christ, demanding they tell her what she seeks. The council narrows progressively — 1,000 then 500 men — until, at **p-f5d1f1**, they single out Judas as the one man who knows the secret. Elene interrogates Judas alone, demanding he reveal "where the Rood of the Sky-King remains, holy under the soil." After he evades her, she has him thrown into a dry well for seven nights without food, until hunger breaks his will and he agrees to reveal the location of the buried crosses.
